{title: Old Wore Out Cowboys}
{artist: Johnny Rodriguez}
{composer: Written by Patsy Bruce and Ronald Robert Peterson}

[C]There must be someplace for [F]old wore out [C]cowboys
Drifters and dreamers and [G7]pickers like [C]me[G7]
Where the [C]cue sticks are straight and the [F]beer’s always [C]cold
And the jukebox is playing [G7]Hank Williams for [C]free[G7]
[C]I’ve worked in poolrooms [F]barrooms and [C]bedrooms
From Cheyenne to Memphis [G7]it ain’t nothing [C]new[G7]
